column5: So last week my wife and I took a quick spin out to Vancouver for some R&R...  Day one....  Stanley Park = Paradise right there . took a pic of a tree growing over a tree Stump .        Day two ...  Drove up to Squamish to see the salmon run , hopped in a raft and slowly drifted Squamish River , missed it by a month or two...                 So if your wondering if theres salmon in the mountains of BC the answer is yes ..    Came across this table used for cleaning way back in the Days  1930 ish    Made of BC fir I guess..     A real Bald Eagle paradise along the river...                 2nd year Juvenile     Day three ...  Whistler Mountians       The rain started to fall and the wind picked up , heres a Blue Heron having a Bad Hair Day .      The next couple of days were back to R&R...
Great looking pictures bud!
Awesome birds, some great captures there.

Those are some awsome pictures!!  It sure is a beautiful area up there, I spent a few months up in victoria last year and caught the tail end of the salmon run and it sure is an amazing site.  Thanks for the pictures!
Nice pics  thanks
I love skulls!!!  Bird and extinct cats and mammoths more, but the fish ain't bad either.
Wow, those are awesome pictures, thanks for sharing them.  Those salmon teeth are huge.  A couple of those head carcasses would be cool to have varnished and put in the den!  Joey
Sweet pics!
Great Pictures, thanks for sharing!!
cool pics
Those are some really nice pics. I had the opportunity to go there last year to visit my brother, what a great experience. Did you get a chance to hike up "The Chief" ? What a mountain!
So much to do and see......so little time to do it...
Spectacular scenery thanks for posting.
Awesome photos!
Great shots, thanks for posting! Not totally sure, but a few of those look like Golden Eagles.
Looks like it was a great trip
Nice pics Paul Beautiful up there!!!  I bet you had plenty of bush for nature walks Was this your first time flying? and was it a direct flight? Thanks for sharing Jacques
Excellent pics Paul!!!  ... but what the heck?... no fishing pics???... you wasted a trip!  ... did they not have any Green Trout for you to molest?
note to self:  book a Bull trip!
This weekend = the first Green trout hard water outing of 2010 , with 24/7 tagging along = should have plenty of GreenBack pics for ya..
Those are some great pics.  That is one place I have always wanted to visit, simply beautiful out there.
I hear ya but those are Juvenile Bald Eagles ...they don't get their White head or White tail feathers until their three years old or so ...
